---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/nav/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/ui/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Documentation — Starmesh"
  description="Starmesh documentation: data sources, transforms, destinations, and support."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="doc-page">
    <h1>Documentation</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>What Is Starmesh?</h2>
      <p>Starmesh is a unified analytics platform that transforms raw unstructured data — like call transcripts, meeting recordings, chats, social media posts, and documents — into structured, analyzable insights.</p>
      <p>We support seamless ingestion from multiple platforms (Zoom, Teams, Gong, Fireflies, Reddit, Google Drive, etc.) and apply advanced AI to extract topics, sentiment, entities, and themes — all without requiring manual effort or custom code.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Capabilities</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Multi-source ingestion:</strong> Connect to audio/video platforms, chat systems, forums, document storage, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>AI-powered transforms:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Topic modeling (guided or unsupervised)</li>
            <li>Sentiment analysis (overall, per speaker, per topic)</li>
            <li>Entity recognition and classification</li>
            <li>Embedding generation and semantic search</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Pipeline builder:</strong> Define reusable data flows from source to transform to storage.</li>
        <li><strong>Export to warehouse:</strong> Write output to BigQuery, GCS, or download as CSV/JSON.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Connecting a Data Source</h2>
      <p>Starmesh supports multiple types of sources. Here's a high-level process to connect one:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to your dashboard → Sources.</li>
        <li>Select the source type (e.g., Zoom, Reddit, Teams, Google Drive).</li>
        <li>Follow the prompts to authenticate (via OAuth, service account, or API token).</li>
        <li>Choose the subset of data you want to analyze (e.g., folders, users, topics, recordings).</li>
        <li>Starmesh will begin ingesting and preprocessing the content.</li>
      </ol>
      <h3>Supported source types include:</h3>
      <table class="doc-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Examples</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Audio/Video platforms</td><td>Zoom, Microsoft Teams, Gong, Fireflies</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Social & forums</td><td>Reddit, Twitter/X, LinkedIn</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Messaging & support</td><td>Intercom, Slack, Salesforce cases</td></tr>
          <tr><td>File & doc storage</td><td>Google Drive, Dropbox, SharePoint</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Email (upcoming)</td><td>Gmail, Outlook</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="doc-note">Note: Not all integrations are available yet. Some source types are coming soon!</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Built-in Transforms</h2>
      <table class="doc-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Transform</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Topic Modeling</td><td>Extract structured topics from conversations or text (LLM or traditional models)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sentiment Analysis</td><td>Detect sentiment per document, per speaker, or by topic</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Entity Recognition</td><td>Identify companies, products, features, competitors, people, and intent</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Embeddings & Search</td><td>Generate dense vector representations for semantic similarity or retrieval</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Custom Prompt Workflows</td><td>Define prompt-based transformations with output schema enforcement</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Destinations</h2>
      <p>Once analyzed, your data can be exported to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google BigQuery</li>
        <li>Google Cloud Storage</li>
        <li>Download</li>
        <li>Upcoming: Snowflake and PostgreSQL</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Testing and Observability</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Preview mode for pipeline testing</li>
        <li>Logs and data flow diagrams</li>
        <li>Versioned runs to compare model configurations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Security and Access Control</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>OAuth 2.0 and service account authentication</li>
        <li>Encryption at rest and in transit</li>
        <li>Fine-grained access control</li>
        <li>No indefinite storage of raw content unless explicitly configured</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Disconnecting a Source or Deleting Data</h2>
      <p>To disconnect a data source:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to Sources tab.</li>
        <li>Click the settings icon for the source.</li>
        <li>Click Revoke Access or Disconnect.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>To delete ingested data, go to Settings → Data Management and request deletion, or email <a href="mailto:support@starmesh.ai">support@starmesh.ai</a>.</p>
      
      <h3>Removing Starmesh from your Zoom Apps</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Log in to your Zoom account and navigate to the Zoom App Marketplace.</li>
        <li>Click Manage >> Added Apps or search for the "Starmesh" app.</li>
        <li>Select the "Starmesh" app.</li>
        <li>Click Remove.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Need Help?</h2>
      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:support@starmesh.ai">support@starmesh.ai</a></p>
      <p>Website: <a href="https://starmesh.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://starmesh.ai</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .doc-page {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 6rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.75rem;
  }

  .doc-page h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366F1, #8B5CF6, #A855F7);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .doc-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #FAFAFA;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.375rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .doc-page h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #FAFAFA;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .doc-page p,
  .doc-page ul,
  .doc-page ol {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #A1A1AA;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .doc-page ul,
  .doc-page ol {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .doc-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .doc-page a {
    color: #818CF8;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .doc-page a:hover {
    color: #A855F7;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .doc-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    background: #111114;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .doc-table th,
  .doc-table td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    text-align: left;
    color: #A1A1AA;
  }

  .doc-table tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .doc-table th {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    color: #FAFAFA;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .doc-table tr:hover td {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
  }

  .doc-note {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #71717A;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border-left: 3px solid rgba(129, 140, 248, 0.7);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .doc-page section {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .doc-page {
      padding: 5rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    .doc-table th,
    .doc-table td {
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
    }
  }
</style> 